0\cdot m=0
\begin{align}0\cdot m+0\cdot m&=(0+0)\cdot m&&\mbox{by the distributive axiom}\\ &=0\cdot m &&\mbox{by the defining property of $0$}\\ (0\cdot m+0\cdot m)+-(0\cdot m)&=0\cdot m+-(0\cdot m)&&\mbox{adding the same quantity to both sides}\\ 0\cdot m+(0\cdot m+-(0\cdot m))&=0\cdot m+-(0\cdot m)&&\mbox{associativity of addition}\\ 0\cdot m+0&=0&&\mbox{defining property of negatives}\\ 0\cdot m&=0&&\mbox{defining property of $0$}\\ \end{align}
